# Domain Layer

Pure, framework-free Dart. Keep it trivially unit-testable.

- No `package:flutter`, `package:drift`, or Riverpod imports here.
- Calculators are stateless static methods or immutable value objects
  (`NetWorthCalculator`, `LinearForecast`, `CurrencyConverter`).
- Currency math goes through `CurrencyConverter`; never multiply raw rates ad hoc.

```dart
// GOOD
final cny = converter.convert(amount: usd, from: Currency.usd, to: Currency.cny);

// BAD: bypasses the rate matrix
final cny = usd * 7.25;
```

- USD is the FX pivot: snapshots store only `USD -> X` rates and
  `CurrencyConverter` derives all cross rates from them. To add a currency, add
  the enum value plus a fallback rate — never special-case pairs.
- FX fallback numbers live in `fx_defaults.dart` as the per-currency
  `kDefaultUsdRates` map (use `defaultUsdRate(currency)` /`defaultUsdRates()`).
  Do not re-hardcode `USD -> X` rates anywhere else.
- Enums in `models/enums.dart` own their own `label(l10n)` / `fromString`
  helpers and data-driven fields (e.g. `Currency.code` / `symbol`); extend
  those rather than scattering `switch` statements.
